{
  "article_id": "LosAngelesTimes1929",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "A fish hook laboriously fashioned by [h]and with a stone implement from a segment of abalone shell, said to [h]ave been used in providing the necessities of life by"
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indian woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "[w]ho, history relates, lived alone on"
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas Island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "for eighteen [y]ears, has been loaned to the"
      },
      {
        "text": "San[t]a Barbara Museum of Natural History",
        "entity_key": "mu_sbmuseum",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "[by]"
      },
      {
        "text": "Mr.",
        "entity_key": "jrock",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "and"
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. John F. Rock",
        "entity_key": "mrsrock",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      },
      {
        "text": "Rock",
        "entity_key": "jrock",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "procured the fish hook, which is [a]bo[ut] half an inch in diameter and shaped much like the figure 5, from"
      },
      {
        "text": "[J]ohn Ogan",
        "entity_key": "jog",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", in whose family it was treasured for more than sixty years [a]n[d] who obtained the treasure from"
      },
      {
        "text": "Capt. Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who rescued"
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "from her long stay alone on"
      },
      {
        "text": "the barren island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", it is said."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "History says that when"
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "were being taken from the"
      },
      {
        "text": "[S]anta Barbara Islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "by govern[m]ent order, since they were unable [t]o obtain a living there,"
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "[wa]s among"
      },
      {
        "text": "those on board",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "the ship",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "[be]ing brought to"
      },
      {
        "text": "this city",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". When [a] long way from"
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "two men [d]iscovered that"
      },
      {
        "text": "her baby",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "had been [o]verlooked and was not on"
      },
      {
        "text": "the [boa]t",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      },
      {
        "text": "The captain",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "chu",
          "isp"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "refused to re[t]urn to",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "for",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the child",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", [so]",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the mother",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "leaped overboard and swam back to",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the boat",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "with the other",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Indians",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "on board, came on to this port.",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "After a time the incident was forgotten. Eighteen years later"
      },
      {
        "text": "Capt. Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "in cruising about"
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", found human tracks in the sand, which he investigated, since"
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "was not supposed to be inhabited, and found"
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indian woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "who had survived the eighteen years without human companionship,"
      },
      {
        "text": "her baby",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "having died."
      }
    ]
  ]
}